             deposed, that the Prisoner brought a Wig to his Master on the 24th of November last to sell; that he askt two Guineas for it, but would have taken 15 s. whereupon his Master stopt it, and sent this Evidence along with the Prisoner to enquire after his Character; that as they went along the Prisoner offer'd him 5 s. to give him a good Character; which he refusing, the Prisner ran away; that the Prosecutor came to their Shop and owned the Wig. 
